{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:galatians.1",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 1 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:1",
      "text": "Paul an apostle—not from men nor through man, but through Jesus Christ and God the Father, who raised him from the dead—",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:2",
      "text": "and all the brethren who are with me, To the churches of Galatia:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:3",
      "text": "Grace to you and peace from God the Father and our Lord Jesus Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:4",
      "text": "who gave himself for our sins to deliver us from the present evil age, according to the will of our God and Father;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:5",
      "text": "to whom be the glory for ever and ever. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:6",
      "text": "I am astonished that you are so quickly deserting him who called you in the grace of Christ and turning to a different gospel—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:7",
      "text": "not that there is another gospel, but there are some who trouble you and want to pervert the gospel of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:8",
      "text": "But even if we, or an angel from heaven, should preach to you a gospel contrary to that which we preached to you, let him be accursed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:9",
      "text": "As we have said before, so now I say again, If any one is preaching to you a gospel contrary to that which you received, let him be accursed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:10",
      "text": "Am I now seeking the favor of men, or of God? Or am I trying to please men? If I were still pleasing men, I should not be a servant of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:11",
      "text": "For I would have you know, brethren, that the gospel which was preached by me is not man's gospel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:12",
      "text": "For I did not receive it from man, nor was I taught it, but it came through a revelation of Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:13",
      "text": "For you have heard of my former life in Judaism, how I persecuted the church of God violently and tried to destroy it;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:14",
      "text": "and I advanced in Judaism beyond many of my own age among my people, so extremely zealous was I for the traditions of my fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:15",
      "text": "But when he who had set me apart before I was born, and had called me through his grace,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:16",
      "text": "was pleased to reveal his Son to me, in order that I might preach him among the Gentiles, I did not confer with flesh and blood,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:17",
      "text": "nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me, but I went away into Arabia; and again I returned to Damascus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:18",
      "text": "Then after three years I went up to Jerusalem to visit Cephas, and remained with him fifteen days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:19",
      "text": "But I saw none of the other apostles except James the Lord's brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:20",
      "text": "(In what I am writing to you, before God, I do not lie!)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:21",
      "text": "Then I went into the regions of Syria and Cilicia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:22",
      "text": "And I was still not known by sight to the churches of Christ in Judea;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:23",
      "text": "they only heard it said, “He who once persecuted us is now preaching the faith he once tried to destroy.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.1.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:24",
      "text": "And they glorified God because of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
